paragraphs.text: in the white room with black curtains near the station. black-roof country, no gold pavement, tired starlings. silver horses run down moonbeams in your dark eyes. dawn-light smiles on you leaving,
my contentment. i'll wait in this place where the sun never shines. wait in this place where the shadows run from them selves.
you said no strings could secure you at the station platform ticket restless diesel goodbye windows i walked into such a sad time at the station as i walked out felt my own need just beginning
